POLOKWANE – One vehicle caught fire after a collision on the N1 south between Mokopane and Mookgophong. According to Transport media liaison officer Mike Maringa the crash involved a VW Sedan and a minibus taxi. Unconfirmed reports suggest the sedan lost control and collided with the minibus taxi. WARNING: GRAPHIC CONTENT N1 before nyl plaza road from joburg road closed due to accident pic.twitter.com/axZDDUufBQ — israel (@israelnema) May 24, 2022  Transport media liaison officer Mike Maringa said the road is partially closed and that motorists using the N1 are advised to drive with extra caution. “More information will be shared once we receive an official report,” he said. Emergency services are currently on the scene. 